                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10044/141.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Leishman says recent uprising in Constantinople is having sequel in other
                    districts and that further trouble seems to be brewing. He adds that massacres
                    at Adana, where there is an American missionary establishment, have been
                    reported, but that he has not been able to confirm the report that two Americans
                    have been killed.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
